---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const APP_URL = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_APP_URL ?? 'https://app.myground.work';
---
<Layout title="How it works · Groundwork" description="Start a Ground, everyone checks in privately, and Groundwork shows where people agree, where they understand things differently, and where a conversation is needed, from a clear beginning to a clear end." canonicalPath="/how-it-works">
  <style>
    *,*::before,*::after{box-sizing:border-box}
    body{margin:0;overflow-x:hidden}
    .gw-nav-link{font-size:13px;font-weight:500;color:#6B6560;background:none;border:none;cursor:pointer;padding:6px 11px;border-radius:6px;font-family:inherit;transition:all .15s;white-space:nowrap;text-decoration:none;display:inline-block;}
    .gw-nav-link:hover{background:#E8E6E3;color:#1A1916;}
    .gw-btn-ghost{font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#0C447C;background:none;border:1px solid #B5D4F4;cursor:pointer;padding:7px 14px;border-radius:6px;font-family:inherit;white-space:nowrap;transition:background .15s;text-decoration:none;display:inline-block;}
    .gw-btn-ghost:hover{background:#EEF4FB;}
    .gw-btn-solid{font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#fff;background:#0C447C;border:none;cursor:pointer;padding:7px 14px;border-radius:6px;font-family:inherit;white-space:nowrap;transition:background .15s;text-decoration:none;display:inline-block;}
    .gw-btn-solid:hover{background:#1557A0;}
    .gw-footer-btn{font-size:12px;color:rgba(255,255,255,.38);background:none;border:none;cursor:pointer;font-family:inherit;text-decoration:none;}
    .gw-footer-btn:hover{color:rgba(255,255,255,.65);}
    @media(max-width:620px){
      .gw-nav-links{display:none !important;}
    }
  </style>

  <div style="font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',sans-serif;background:#EDECEA;min-height:100vh;color:#1A1916;">

    <nav style="position:sticky;top:0;z-index:100;background:rgba(237,236,234,.96);backdrop-filter:blur(8px);border-bottom:1px solid #E2E0DB;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;padding:0 20px;height:56px;">
      <a href="/" style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:9px;text-decoration:none;">
        <svg width="20" height="16" viewBox="0 0 22 17" fill="none">
          <rect x="5"  y="0"  width="12" height="3" rx="1.5" fill="#0C447C" opacity="0.45"/>
          <rect x="2"  y="6"  width="18" height="3" rx="1.5" fill="#0C447C" opacity="0.72"/>
          <rect x="0"  y="12" width="22" height="3" rx="1.5" fill="#0C447C"/>
        </svg>
        <span style="font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:#0C447C;letter-spacing:-.02em;">Groundwork</span>
      </a>
      <div class="gw-nav-links" style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:2px;">
        <a class="gw-nav-link" href="/">Home</a>
        <a class="gw-nav-link" href="/how-it-works" style="background:#E8E6E3;color:#1A1916;">How it works</a>
        <a class="gw-nav-link" href="/pricing">Pricing</a>
        <a class="gw-nav-link" href="/about">About</a>
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;flex-shrink:0;">
        <a class="gw-btn-ghost" href={`${APP_URL}/auth`}>Sign in</a>
        <a class="gw-btn-solid" href={`${APP_URL}/start`}>Get started free</a>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <main style="max-width:600px;margin:0 auto;padding:56px 24px 80px;">
      <p style="font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#0C447C;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:12px;">How it works</p>
      <h1 style="font-size:32px;font-weight:800;color:#1A1916;line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:16px;">How Groundwork works.</h1>
      <p style="font-size:16px;color:#6B6560;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:48px;">Every Ground follows the same simple path, from a clear beginning to a clear end.</p>

      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0;margin-bottom:48px;">
        <div style="display:flex;gap:20px;padding:24px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E0DB;">
          <div style="width:36px;height:36px;background:#0C447C;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;font-size:16px;font-weight:800;color:#fff;">1</div>
          <div>
            <div style="font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#1A1916;margin-bottom:6px;">Start a Ground</div>
            <div style="font-size:14px;color:#6B6560;line-height:1.7;">Start one for an important piece of work where expectations, responsibilities, or delivery are easy to lose track of, or when something already underway does not feel right. You do not have to start at the very beginning. The manager sets the starting point: the objectives, what success looks like, expectations, responsibilities, constraints, and the context that matters. This becomes the baseline the rest of the Ground is measured against.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;gap:20px;padding:24px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E0DB;">
          <div style="width:36px;height:36px;background:#0C447C;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;font-size:16px;font-weight:800;color:#fff;">2</div>
          <div>
            <div style="font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#1A1916;margin-bottom:6px;">Invite the people involved</div>
            <div style="font-size:14px;color:#6B6560;line-height:1.7;">Invite everyone involved: managers, employees, partners, and stakeholders. Everyone checks in on their own so every person gets the same chance to contribute, regardless of confidence, personality, communication style, or seniority.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;gap:20px;padding:24px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E0DB;">
          <div style="width:36px;height:36px;background:#0C447C;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;font-size:16px;font-weight:800;color:#fff;">3</div>
          <div>
            <div style="font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#1A1916;margin-bottom:6px;">What stays private, what is shared</div>
            <div style="font-size:14px;color:#6B6560;line-height:1.7;">Your check-in stays private to you. Groundwork uses everyone's responses to build the shared report, which shows where people agree, where they understand things differently, and what needs attention. It never shows anyone's raw answers, and it never identifies who said what about another person. The shared report appears once everyone has checked in. This is what makes people comfortable being honest, which is what makes the Ground worth having.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;gap:20px;padding:24px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E0DB;">
          <div style="width:36px;height:36px;background:#0C447C;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;font-size:16px;font-weight:800;color:#fff;">4</div>
          <div>
            <div style="font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#1A1916;margin-bottom:6px;">Check in as the work goes on</div>
            <div style="font-size:14px;color:#6B6560;line-height:1.7;">Groundwork runs regular check-ins and prompts people automatically when it is their turn, so you are not left chasing anyone. Each one records where things stand: progress, priorities, changes, commitments, risks, concerns, and any evidence. A check-in takes about ten minutes.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;gap:20px;padding:24px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E0DB;">
          <div style="width:36px;height:36px;background:#0C447C;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;font-size:16px;font-weight:800;color:#fff;">5</div>
          <div>
            <div style="font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#1A1916;margin-bottom:6px;">Groundwork compares the whole picture</div>
            <div style="font-size:14px;color:#6B6560;line-height:1.7;">At every check-in, Groundwork compares what people are saying now with what was agreed at the beginning, what they said before, and the evidence they have provided. It shows the things that are hard to see through meetings and documents alone: expectations that have changed, risks starting to show, work falling behind, unclear ownership, and where a conversation is needed. For example: "Two people described different agreed deadlines. Shown at check-in 2, before the deadline passed."</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;gap:20px;padding:24px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #E2E0DB;">
          <div style="width:36px;height:36px;background:#0C447C;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;font-size:16px;font-weight:800;color:#fff;">6</div>
          <div>
            <div style="font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#1A1916;margin-bottom:6px;">Read the reports, and take them into your calls</div>
            <div style="font-size:14px;color:#6B6560;line-height:1.7;">Managers get reports showing progress against the objectives, what has changed, risks, where expectations differ, delivery against commitments, and the conversations worth having now. Groundwork does not replace your one-to-ones. Take the report into them, so the meeting is spent on the conversation, not the catch-up.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;gap:20px;padding:24px 0;">
          <div style="width:36px;height:36px;background:#085041;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;font-size:16px;font-weight:800;color:#fff;">7</div>
          <div>
            <div style="font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#1A1916;margin-bottom:6px;">Close the Ground</div>
            <div style="font-size:14px;color:#6B6560;line-height:1.7;">When the work reaches its end, Groundwork compares the final outcome with the starting point and produces a clear conclusion: objectives against what was delivered, how expectations changed, the key decisions, the evidence, what was learned, and the complete history of the Ground. Every Ground gives the next manager, team, or project a clearer place to start.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="background:#F5F3EF;border-radius:10px;padding:24px;border-left:3px solid #0C447C;margin-bottom:40px;">
        <h3 style="font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#1A1916;margin-bottom:8px;">Alignment status</h3>
        <p style="font-size:13px;color:#6B6560;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:16px;">Every report carries a clear read on where things stand. It is not a grade out of five. It is a plain summary of how many areas are aligned, how many are partly there, and how many are still open.</p>
        <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(5,1fr);gap:8px;">
          <div style="text-align:center;padding:10px 6px;background:white;border-radius:6px;border:1px solid #E2E0DB;"><div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:#8A5C1A;">Unresolved</div></div>
          <div style="text-align:center;padding:10px 6px;background:white;border-radius:6px;border:1px solid #E2E0DB;"><div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:#9B9590;">Mixed</div></div>
          <div style="text-align:center;padding:10px 6px;background:white;border-radius:6px;border:1px solid #E2E0DB;"><div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:#0C447C;">Emerging</div></div>
          <div style="text-align:center;padding:10px 6px;background:white;border-radius:6px;border:1px solid #E2E0DB;"><div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:#0C447C;">Clear</div></div>
          <div style="text-align:center;padding:10px 6px;background:#085041;border-radius:6px;"><div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:white;">Aligned</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="background:#EEF4FB;border:1px solid #B5D4F4;border-radius:10px;padding:16px 20px;margin-bottom:40px;">
        <p style="font-size:13px;color:#0C447C;line-height:1.7;margin:0;"><b>Groundwork supports the manager, it does not replace them.</b> It does not decide who was right or evaluate personalities and communication styles. It helps managers understand what happened, what has changed, and where a conversation is needed. Managers still make the decisions.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="text-align:center;">
        <a class="gw-btn-solid" href={`${APP_URL}/start`} style="padding:13px 28px;font-size:14px;">Start your first Ground</a>
      </div>
    </main>

    <footer style="background:#0A1628;padding:32px 24px;text-align:center;">
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:9px;margin-bottom:16px;">
        <svg width="18" height="14" viewBox="0 0 22 17" fill="none">
          <rect x="5"  y="0"  width="12" height="3" rx="1.5" fill="white" opacity="0.45"/>
          <rect x="2"  y="6"  width="18" height="3" rx="1.5" fill="white" opacity="0.72"/>
          <rect x="0"  y="12" width="22" height="3" rx="1.5" fill="white"/>
        </svg>
        <span style="font-size:14px;font-weight:700;color:rgba(255,255,255,.85);">Groundwork</span>
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:16px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-bottom:20px;">
        <a class="gw-footer-btn" href="/">Home</a>
        <a class="gw-footer-btn" href="/how-it-works">How it works</a>
        <a class="gw-footer-btn" href="/use-cases">Use cases</a>
        <a class="gw-footer-btn" href="/pricing">Pricing</a>
        <a class="gw-footer-btn" href="/about">About</a>
      </div>
      <p style="font-size:11px;color:rgba(255,255,255,.2);margin:0;">&#169; 2025 Groundwork.</p>
    </footer>

  </div>
</Layout>
